# =============================================================================
# neural-forge mandatory .gitignore baseline
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Every project under projects/ and the monorepo root MUST include every
# pattern in this file. The CI workflow .github/workflows/gitignore-baseline.yml
# and the local pre-commit hook enforce this.
#
# Rationale is recorded in docs/adr/0002-gitignore-baseline.md. Do not remove
# or weaken any entry without first updating the ADR.
# =============================================================================

# --- Data: versioned via DVC, never git ------------------------------------
# GitHub rejects files > 100 MB and performs poorly with binary blobs.
# All dataset formats (CSV, Parquet, images, audio, etc.) belong in DVC.
#
# Pattern rationale: `data/` alone would exclude the directory as a whole
# and git would stop recursing, so `!data/**/.gitkeep` re-includes would
# never fire. Using `data/**` ignores every file under data/ at any depth
# while still letting git walk the tree; `!data/**/` keeps subdirectories
# traversable; `!data/**/.gitkeep` tracks the sentinel files that preserve
# the empty-directory structure across clones; and `!data/**/*.dvc`
# re-includes DVC pointer files, which MUST be committed — otherwise
# `dvc add` of any file under `data/` fails with
# `bad DVC file name '...' is git-ignored`.
data/**
!data/**/
!data/**/.gitkeep
!data/**/*.dvc

# --- Secrets: never, under any circumstance, commit -----------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
credentials.json

# --- Python local artifacts -----------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

